he ConfigDef instance\n\n### Major Config Classes (46 total found)\n\n**Clients Module:**\n- AdminClientConfig - Client admin operations configuration\n- ConsumerConfig - Consumer client configuration\n- ProducerConfig - Producer client configuration\n- BrokerSecurityConfigs - Security-related configurations\n\n**Server Module:**\n- AbstractKafkaConfig - Base configuration for Kafka servers\n- KRaftConfigs - KRaft mode configurations\n- ServerConfigs - Core server configurations\n- SocketServerConfigs - Network/socket configurations\n- ClientMetricsConfigs - Client metrics tracking\n- MetricConfigs - JMX and metrics configurations\n- DelegationTokenManagerConfigs - Token management\n- ReplicationConfigs - Replication parameters\n\n**Streams Module:**\n- StreamsConfig - Kafka Streams application configuration\n- TopologyConfig - Topology-specific settings\n\n**Connect Module:**\n- WorkerConfig - Kafka Connect worker configuration (base)\n- ConnectorConfig - Base connector configuration\n- SourceConnectorConfig - Source-specific configuration\n- SinkConnectorConfig - Sink-specific configuration\n- TaskConfig - Task configuration\n- RestServerConfig - REST endpoint configuration\n- StandaloneConfig - Standalone worker configuration\n- DistributedConfig - Distributed worker configuration\n- SimpleConfig - Simplified configuration wrapper\n- MirrorClientConfig, MirrorConnectorConfig, MirrorMakerConfig - Mirror Maker configurations\n\n**Coordinator Modules:**\n- GroupCoordinatorConfig - Consumer group coordination\n- GroupConfig - Group-level settings\n- ShareGroupConfig - Share group settings\n- ShareCoordinatorConfig - Share group coordination\n- TransactionLogConfig, TransactionStateManagerConfig, AddPartitionsToTxnConfig - Transaction management\n\n**Storage/Log Module:**\n- LogConfig - Topic log configuration\n- CleanerConfig - Log cleaner configuration\n- RemoteLogManagerConfig - Remote log tier storage\n\n**Raft Module:**\n- QuorumConfig - Raft quorum configuration\n- MetadataLogConfig - Metadata log configuration\n\n### Documentation Generation Chain\n\nThe documentation generation system works through:\n1. ConfigDef.toHtml() method converts config metadata to HTML\n2. Used by KafkaConfig.main() to generate broker config docs\n3. Used by StreamsConfig.main() to generate streams config docs\n4. Used by ConsumerConfig, ProducerConfig, LogConfig main methods\n5. Used by ConnectorConfig documentation system\n\nThis pattern allows centralized, consistent configuration documentation generation from the same metadata source."
